abstract: The messengers who were sent to Orleans, yesterday, where the battle was going on, have returned. They make the following report: THE BATTLE OF TUESDAY. abstract: The sad consequences which excessive love of drink leads to frequently, was illustrated in a case which came up in the Yorkville Police Court, yesterday. abstract: About a year ago GEORGE H. HODDER was carrying on the boot and shoo business in Newark, and JAMES P. DONNELLY was one of his employes. HODDER becoming deeply involved, was sold out at Sheriffs sale, DONNELLY being the purchasser. It was supposed by those Interested that HODDER'S money was used for the purpose, and that he was still the real proprietor.

abstract: The Provisional Government has issued a proclamation to the French people denouncing the surrender of Metz as an act of treason, and urging the French to renewed efforts.
